'''PKNIC''' is the [[.pk]] domain name registry in the [[Pakistan]], it was started by a [[Pakistani American]] [[Ashar Nisar]] in June 1992. The company is operated as a self-supporting organization.<ref>[http://www.pknic.net.pk/ "PKNIC Website"]</ref> PKNIC is managed and owned by an American-based company started by a Pakistani American. Up until July 2009, there were no [[.PK]] [[root servers]] inside [[Pakistan]], numerous attempts were made in the past to bring [[.pk]] operations to [[Pakistan]]. A Pakistani Newspaper DAWN now reports that the Government, working through the [[Pakistan Telecommunication Authority|PTA]], has somehow managed to convince the owner of '''PKNIC''' to open an office in [[Lahore]] and deploy a mirrored [[root server]] (m-2.pknic.net.pk) in what once used to be his hometown.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/wps/wcm/connect/dawn-content-library/dawn/news/business/11-pknic-to-set-up-office-in-lahore--il--05|title=PKNIC to set up office in Lahore |date=July 18, 2009|publisher=Dawn|accessdate=20 March 2010}}</ref>
